snippet: Muhammad Tahir-ul Qadri failed to achieve his headline aims, like the immediate dissolution of President Asif Ali Zardari’s government.
abstract: Muhammad Tahir-ul Qadri, preacher turned political activist who led thousands of supporters in march on Islamabad, ends his protest after government grants his Awami Tehreek party largely symbolic input into Pakistan’s electoral process; Qadri fails to achieve his headline aims, such as immediate dissolution of President Asif Ali Zardari’s government, but manages to gain unusually prominent role for political outsider.

byline.original: By DECLAN WALSH and SALMAN MASOOD

lead_paragraph: Muhammad Tahir-ul Qadri failed to achieve his headline aims, like the immediate dissolution of President Asif Ali Zardari’s government.

headline.seo: Pakistani Preacher Ends Protest in Government Deal
